polynomial

Class PolynomialNodeElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • polynomial.PolynomialNodeElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PolynomialNode

    public class PolynomialNodeElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements PolynomialNode
    This represents a node for the list containing the polynomial. This is part of a list containing multiple terms of polynomials.

      • addTerm

        public PolynomialNode addTerm(ComparePower comparator,
                              PolynomialTerm insert)
        Adds a node to the list, based on the power of the term. The higher terms added towards the beginning of the list.
        Specified by:
        addTerm in interface PolynomialNode
        Parameters:
        comparator - A class containing the formula to compare the degree of two polynomials.
        insert - The polynomial term to insert.
        Returns:
        Return a new node into the list. If there is a node with the same power, this will add the coefficients of the two polynomials, and the polynomial term in the list will be mutated.
